{"action":"opened","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/4876","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/4876/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/4876/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/4876/events","html_url":"https://github.com/lfortran/lfortran/issues/4876","id":2541092637,"node_id":"I_kwDOCpMuHc6Xdf8d","number":4876,"title":"pass_manager: apply only relevant passes","user":{"login":"kp992","id":145801876,"node_id":"U_kgDOCLDClA","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/145801876?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/kp992","html_url":"https://github.com/kp992","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kp992/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kp992/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kp992/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kp992/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kp992/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kp992/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kp992/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kp992/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kp992/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2024-09-22T13:55:16Z","updated_at":"2024-09-22T13:55:16Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"The current [pass_manager implementation](https://github.com/lfortran/lfortran/blob/main/src/libasr/pass/pass_manager.h#L304) shows that we are apply all the passes while compiling front-end code.  We can optimize the same by adding some flag during generation of ASR. For example, `print_list_tuple` should only be set to true when we have either `list` or `tuple` ASR node while generation.

This may be a small optimization but once the number of passes start to grow, I think this can play a significant role in avoid visiting the large ASR again and again for no use.

